## AI Signal Codebase Specifics

### Schema patterns
Recently added: `editorial_take`, `broadcast_phrases`. Both nullable.
Migration pattern: `ALTER TABLE stories ADD COLUMN X NULL`.
Watch for forgotten type updates in `db/types/database.ts` (Row + Insert + Update).

### Component tree
```
page.tsx → HomePageClient → HeroZone → HeroBroadcast
                          → StoryArticle / StoryCard
```
Props thread through all layers. Forgotten thread = silent prop loss.

### Cascade architecture
```
Writer → Validator (Layer 1) →
  PASS: write to DB
  FAIL: Haiku Fixer (Layer 2, gets violations) →
    PASS after Haiku: write
    FAIL: Sonnet Reviewer (Layer 3, NOW gets violations after recent fix) →
      Final re-validation logs persistent violations → write anyway
```

### Validator checks
13 checks currently. Each new field needing enforcement should add a Check N.
Don't create silent quality gaps.

### Journalist prompts — 3-place sync
- `src/lib/prompts.ts`
- `src/app/api/cron/daily-signal/route.ts` SYSTEM_PROMPT
- `src/lib/journalist-agent.ts` GeneratedSignal interface + JSON_SCHEMA

All three must align. New field added in one place but missing in another =
silent runtime bug.

### Component fragility
StoryArticle.tsx is 1643 lines. Past bug: duplicate `<article>` blocks from
str_replace double-apply. Always verify single return block in any
StoryArticle edit.

### Backup branch convention
Before major changes: `git branch <branch-name>-backup-<reason>`
Rollback: `git reset --hard <backup-branch>`

---

## What This Agent Does NOT Do

- Design new features → use main agent or think-and-build
- Brainstorm ideas → use main agent
- Pure execution → use main agent (this agent reviews execution)
- Debug without a diff → working chat directly

If user asks "should I build X" → main agent.
If user pastes diff and says "review" → this agent.
